<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/public/css/style.css" />
    <title>PicIt!</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="title-container">
      <h1 class="title">PICIT</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="usage-container">
      <p class="how-to-use">HOW TO USE:</p><br>
      <p class="how-to-use">1. Upload a picture from your local library.</p><br>
      <p class="how-to-use">2. It will show the words analized on the scree.</p><br>
      <p class="how-to-use">3. Delete the words that you alreay know.</p><br>
      <p class="how-to-use">4. Save the words for later study!</p><br>
    </div>
    <form
      action="/result"
      method="POST"
      enctype="multipart/form-data"
      class="form-container"
    >
      <input type="file" name="image" class="upload-img" />
      <button type="submit" class="submit-btn">Upload</button>
    </form>
    <div class="project-desc-container">
      <p class="about-project">* PicIt! is a wep/app project developed by Jiwoong Shinn and Sungwon Yuk. PicIt! provides language analysis of a picture with texts, combined with Natural Language Processing (also known as NLP). Once it finishes the analysis, it searches the words' definition on the web and shows them to the user. Thank you for visiting the webpage.</p>
    </div>
      <div class="footer-container">
        <marquee class="footer" behavior="scroll">
          Developed by Jiwoong Shinn, Sungwon Yuk. As a part of the graduation project @SEOULTECH.
        </marquee>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
